e existing hierarchies. They expose the consequences of and reactions to grand EU-restructuring policies, which at times threaten to turn the countryside into a manicured playground for escapee urbanites. This book will appeal to anyone seriously interested in the realities of rural life today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSociology, RuralzEurope. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aRural anthropology.  aWestern Europe.1 aCollinson, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrenn, Chantal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernández De Larrinoa, Kepa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreire Paz, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacClancy, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacclancy, Jeremy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartínez Montoya, Josetxu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStacul, Jaro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526137098zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526137098zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526137098/original  a978-3-11-128311-1 Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA